# API Gateway Service (Spring Cloud Gateway)

Applies under `services/api-gateway-service/`.

## Role

1. Sole (or primary) public HTTP entry for `/api/v1/ai/**` per `docs/contracts/gateway-proxy.md`.
2. Validate platform JWT (when `gateway.dev-mode=false`); in dev mode, allow `X-User-Id` without JWT as documented.
3. Strip `Authorization` from upstream Proxy requests; attach `X-Gateway-Auth`, `X-User-Id`, optional org/team headers.

## Implementation

1. Prefer declarative routes in `application.yml`; use `GATEWAY_PROXY_URI` for Proxy base URL when environments differ.
2. Global filters that mutate requests should preserve streaming-related headers where needed.
3. Do not log raw JWT or shared secrets.
4. **`GATEWAY_SHARED_SECRET`:** non-empty at runtime (`GatewayStartupValidation`). In Docker Compose, if the env var is set to an **empty string**, Spring may not fall back to `application.yml` defaults — align with Proxy and usage-service; see `docs/contracts/gateway-proxy.md` §5.1.
